{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, efficiency may not only be required for training but also for prediction.",
    "In MCDA, scalability is, usually, less critical because the computation of a preference model involves a much smaller volume of data.",
    "In the case of multiobjective optimization concerning complex (nonlinear or combinatorial) problems, a short computation time is required between successive sessions of interactions with the DM.",
    "• Application domains Preferences in general and preference learning in particular play an increasingly important role in various domains of application, ranging from computational advertising, recommender systems, electronic commerce, and computer games to adaptive user interfaces and personalized medicine.",
    "PL is also used in social media and platforms such as TikTok, YouTube, Spotify, LinkedIn, etc., again mainly for the purpose of personalization."
  ]
}